As Cho'Gath you won't always be in a winning position though. You win most match-ups by ==attrition==, losing at first, but slowly getting the ==resource advantage== through your passive.&#x20;
* Your <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey="Q" />'s mana cost is fairly low, making it a great tool to ==CS at range==, while waiting for the wave to come into you.
* ==IMPORTANT:== You need a ==normal cast== bind for your <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey="Q" /> so you can actually see the **indicator**. When you cast <ScAbilityInline_v2 spellKey="Q" />, you want to aim it so it only hits the ==low HP minions==, or you'll grief your wave and push it into your opponent.
* As Cho'gath, it's almost impossible to get pushed out of lane as long as you let the wave come into you, CS'ing under tower, constantly getting ==health and mana back==.
* But if you mess up and push into your opponent while you're at like ==50% HP==, and they get to ==freeze==, that's the one way you can actually get big time punished.&#x20;
